{"type": "USJ", "version": "3.1", "content": [{"type": "book", "marker": "id", "content": ["60-1PE-web.sfm English Arabic Names Version (EANV)"], "code": "1PE"}, {"type": "para", "marker": "ide", "content": ["UTF-8\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "h", "content": ["1 Peter \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "toc1", "content": ["Peter\u2019s First Letter \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "toc2", "content": ["1 Peter \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "toc3", "content": ["1Pe \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "mt1", "content": ["Peter\u2019s First Letter \n"]}, {"type": "chapter", "marker": "c", "number": "1", "sid": "1PE 1"}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "1", "sid": "1PE 1:1"}, "Peter, an apostle of Al Masih Isa, to the chosen ones who are living as foreigners in the Dispersion in Pontus, Galatia,\nCappadocia, Asia, and Bithynia, \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "2", "sid": "1PE 1:2"}, "according to the foreknowledge of Allah the Father, in sanctification of the Spirit, that you may obey Al Masih Isa and be\nsprinkled with his blood: Grace to you and peace be multiplied. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "3", "sid": "1PE 1:3"}, "Blessed be Allah and Father of our Lord Al Masih Isa, who according to his great mercy caused us to be born again to a\nliving hope through the resurrection of Al Masih Isa from the dead,\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "4", "sid": "1PE 1:4"}, "to an incorruptible and undefiled inheritance that doesn\u2019t fade away, reserved in Heaven for you,\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "5", "sid": "1PE 1:5"}, "who by the power of Allah are guarded through faith for a salvation ready to be revealed in the last time.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "6", "sid": "1PE 1:6"}, "Wherein you greatly rejoice, though now for a little while, if need be, you have been grieved in various trials,\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "7", "sid": "1PE 1:7"}, "that the proof of your faith, which is more precious than gold that perishes even though it is tested by fire, may be\nfound to result in praise, glory, and honour at the revelation of Al Masih Isa\u2014\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "8", "sid": "1PE 1:8"}, "whom, not having known, you love. In him, though now you don\u2019t see him, yet believing, you rejoice greatly with joy that\nis unspeakable and full of glory, \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "9", "sid": "1PE 1:9"}, "receiving the result of your faith, the salvation of your souls.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "10", "sid": "1PE 1:10"}, "Concerning this salvation, the prophets sought and searched diligently. They prophesied of the grace that would come to\nyou, \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "11", "sid": "1PE 1:11"}, "searching for who or what kind of time the Spirit of Masih, which was in them, pointed to, when he predicted the\nsufferings of Masih, and the glories that would follow them. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "12", "sid": "1PE 1:12"}, "To them it was revealed, that they served not to themselves, but to you, in these things, which now have been announced\nto you through those who preached the Good News to you by the Holy Spirit sent out from heaven; which things angels desire to\nlook into. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "13", "sid": "1PE 1:13"}, "Therefore prepare your minds for action.", {"type": "note", "marker": "f", "content": ["  ", {"type": "char", "marker": "fr", "content": ["1:13 "]}, {"type": "char", "marker": "ft", "content": ["literally, \u201cgird up the waist of your mind\u201d or \u201cput on the\nbelt of the waist of your mind\u201d"]}], "caller": "+"}, " Be sober, and set your hope fully on the grace that will be brought to you at the revelation\nof Al Masih Isa\u2014 \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "14", "sid": "1PE 1:14"}, "as children of obedience, not conforming yourselves according to your former lusts as in your ignorance,\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "15", "sid": "1PE 1:15"}, "but just as he who called you is holy, you yourselves also be holy in all of your behaviour;\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "16", "sid": "1PE 1:16"}, "because it is written, \u201cYou shall be holy; for I am holy.\u201d", {"type": "note", "marker": "x", "content": [{"type": "char", "marker": "xo", "content": ["1:16 "]}, {"type": "char", "marker": "xt", "content": ["Leviticus 11:44-45"]}], "caller": "+"}, " \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "17", "sid": "1PE 1:17"}, "If you call on him as Father, who without respect of persons judges according to each man\u2019s work, pass the time of your\nliving as foreigners here in reverent fear, \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "18", "sid": "1PE 1:18"}, "knowing that you were redeemed, not with corruptible things, with silver or gold, from the useless way of life handed\ndown from your fathers, \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "19", "sid": "1PE 1:19"}, "but with precious blood, as of a lamb without blemish or spot, the blood of Masih,\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "20", "sid": "1PE 1:20"}, "who was foreknown indeed before the foundation of the world, but was revealed in this last age for your sake,\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "21", "sid": "1PE 1:21"}, "who through him are believers in Allah, who raised him from the dead, and gave him glory, so that your faith and hope\nmight be in Allah. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "22", "sid": "1PE 1:22"}, "Seeing you have purified your souls in your obedience to the truth through the Spirit in sincere brotherly affection,\nlove one another from the heart fervently, \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "23", "sid": "1PE 1:23"}, "having been born again, not of corruptible seed, but of incorruptible, through the word of Allah, which lives and remains\nforever. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "24", "sid": "1PE 1:24"}, "For, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": ["\u201cAll flesh is like grass, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["and all of man\u2019s glory like the flower in the grass. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": ["The grass withers, and its flower falls; \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "25", "sid": "1PE 1:25"}, "but the Lord\u2019s word endures forever.\u201d", {"type": "note", "marker": "x", "content": [{"type": "char", "marker": "xo", "content": ["1:25 "]}, {"type": "char", "marker": "xt", "content": ["Isaiah\n40:6-8"]}], "caller": "+"}, " \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": ["This is the word of Good News which was preached to you. \n"]}, {"type": "chapter", "marker": "c", "number": "2", "sid": "1PE 2"}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "1", "sid": "1PE 2:1"}, "Putting away therefore all wickedness, all deceit, hypocrisies, envies, and all evil speaking,\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "2", "sid": "1PE 2:2"}, "as newborn babies, long for the pure milk of the Word, that with it you may grow,\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "3", "sid": "1PE 2:3"}, "if indeed you have tasted that the Lord is gracious: \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "4", "sid": "1PE 2:4"}, "coming to him, a living stone, rejected indeed by men, but chosen by Allah, precious.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "5", "sid": "1PE 2:5"}, "You also, as living stones, are built up as a spiritual house, to be a holy priesthood, to offer up spiritual sacrifices,\nacceptable to Allah through Al Masih Isa. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "6", "sid": "1PE 2:6"}, "Because it is contained in Scripture, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": ["\u201cBehold,", {"type": "note", "marker": "f", "content": ["  ", {"type": "char", "marker": "fr", "content": ["2:6 "]}, {"type": "char", "marker": "ft", "content": ["\u201cBehold\u201d, from \u201c\u05d4\u05b4\u05e0\u05bc\u05b5\u05d4\u201d or \u201c\u1f30\u03b4\u03bf\u1f7a\u201d, means look at, take notice, observe, see, or gaze at. It is\noften used as an interjection."]}], "caller": "+"}, " I lay in Zion a chief cornerstone, chosen and precious:\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["He who believes in him will not be disappointed.\u201d", {"type": "note", "marker": "x", "content": [{"type": "char", "marker": "xo", "content": ["2:6\n"]}, {"type": "char", "marker": "xt", "content": ["Isaiah 28:16 "]}], "caller": "+"}, " \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "7", "sid": "1PE 2:7"}, "For you who believe therefore is the honour, but for those who are disobedient,\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": ["\u201cThe stone which the builders rejected \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["has become the chief cornerstone,\u201d", {"type": "note", "marker": "x", "content": [{"type": "char", "marker": "xo", "content": ["2:7 "]}, {"type": "char", "marker": "xt", "content": ["Zabur 118:22"]}], "caller": "+"}, "\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "8", "sid": "1PE 2:8"}, "and, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": ["\u201ca stumbling stone and a rock of offence.\u201d", {"type": "note", "marker": "x", "content": [{"type": "char", "marker": "xo", "content": ["2:8 "]}, {"type": "char", "marker": "xt", "content": ["Isaiah\n8:14"]}], "caller": "+"}, " \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": ["For they stumble at the word, being disobedient, to which also they were appointed.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "9", "sid": "1PE 2:9"}, "But you are a chosen race, a royal priesthood, a holy nation, a people for Allah\u2019s own possession, that you may proclaim\nthe excellence of him who called you out of darkness into his marvellous light.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "10", "sid": "1PE 2:10"}, "In the past, you were not a people, but now are Allah\u2019s people, who had not obtained mercy, but now have obtained mercy.\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "11", "sid": "1PE 2:11"}, "Beloved, I beg you as foreigners and pilgrims, to abstain from fleshly lusts, which war against the soul;\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "12", "sid": "1PE 2:12"}, "having good behaviour amongst the nations, so in that of which they speak against you as evildoers, they may by your good\nworks, which they see, glorify Allah in the day of visitation. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "13", "sid": "1PE 2:13"}, "Therefore subject yourselves to every ordinance of man for the Lord\u2019s sake: whether to the king, as supreme;\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "14", "sid": "1PE 2:14"}, "or to governors, as sent by him for vengeance on evildoers and for praise to those who do well.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "15", "sid": "1PE 2:15"}, "For this is the will of Allah, that by well-doing you should put to silence the ignorance of foolish men:\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "16", "sid": "1PE 2:16"}, "as free, and not using your freedom for a cloak of wickedness, but as bondservants of Allah.\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "17", "sid": "1PE 2:17"}, "Honour all men. Love the brotherhood. Fear Allah. Honour the king.\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "18", "sid": "1PE 2:18"}, "Servants, be in subjection to your masters with all respect: not only to the good and gentle, but also to the wicked.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "19", "sid": "1PE 2:19"}, "For it is commendable if someone endures pain, suffering unjustly, because of conscience towards Allah.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "20", "sid": "1PE 2:20"}, "For what glory is it if, when you sin, you patiently endure beating? But if, when you do well, you patiently endure\nsuffering, this is commendable with Allah. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "21", "sid": "1PE 2:21"}, "For you were called to this, because Masih also suffered for us, leaving\nyou", {"type": "note", "marker": "f", "content": ["  ", {"type": "char", "marker": "fr", "content": ["2:21 "]}, {"type": "char", "marker": "ft", "content": ["TR reads \u201cus\u201d instead of \u201cyou\u201d"]}], "caller": "+"}, " an example, that you should follow his steps,\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "22", "sid": "1PE 2:22"}, "who didn\u2019t sin, \u201cneither was deceit found in his mouth.\u201d", {"type": "note", "marker": "x", "content": [{"type": "char", "marker": "xo", "content": ["2:22 "]}, {"type": "char", "marker": "xt", "content": ["Isaiah 53:9"]}], "caller": "+"}, " \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "23", "sid": "1PE 2:23"}, "When he was cursed, he didn\u2019t curse back. When he suffered, he didn\u2019t threaten, but committed himself to him who judges\nrighteously. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "24", "sid": "1PE 2:24"}, "He himself bore our sins in his body on the tree, that we, having died to sins, might live to righteousness. You were\nhealed by his wounds.", {"type": "note", "marker": "f", "content": ["  ", {"type": "char", "marker": "fr", "content": ["2:24 "]}, {"type": "char", "marker": "ft", "content": ["or, stripes"]}], "caller": "+"}, " \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "25", "sid": "1PE 2:25"}, "For you were going astray like sheep; but now you have returned to the Shepherd and\nOverseer", {"type": "note", "marker": "f", "content": ["  ", {"type": "char", "marker": "fr", "content": ["2:25 "]}, {"type": "char", "marker": "ft", "content": ["\u201cOverseer\u201d is from the Greek \u1f10\u03c0\u03af\u03c3\u03ba\u03bf\u03c0\u03bf\u03bd, which can mean overseer, curator, guardian, or\nsuperintendent."]}], "caller": "+"}, " of your souls. \n"]}, {"type": "chapter", "marker": "c", "number": "3", "sid": "1PE 3"}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "1", "sid": "1PE 3:1"}, "In the same way, wives, be in subjection to your own husbands; so that, even if any don\u2019t obey the Word, they may be won\nby the behaviour of their wives without a word, \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "2", "sid": "1PE 3:2"}, "seeing your pure behaviour in fear. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "3", "sid": "1PE 3:3"}, "Let your beauty be not just the outward adorning of braiding the hair, and of wearing jewels of gold, or of putting on\nfine clothing; \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "4", "sid": "1PE 3:4"}, "but in the hidden person of the heart, in the incorruptible adornment of a gentle and quiet spirit, which is very precious\nin the sight of Allah. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "5", "sid": "1PE 3:5"}, "For this is how in the past, the holy women who hoped in Allah also adorned themselves, being in subjection to their own\nhusbands. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "6", "sid": "1PE 3:6"}, "So Sarah obeyed Ibrahim, calling him lord, whose children you now are, if you do well, and are not put in fear by any\nterror. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "7", "sid": "1PE 3:7"}, "You husbands, in the same way, live with your wives according to knowledge, giving honour to the woman, as to the weaker\nvessel, as also being joint heirs of the grace of life, that your prayers may not be hindered.\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "8", "sid": "1PE 3:8"}, "Finally, all of you be like-minded, compassionate, loving as brothers, tenderhearted, courteous,\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "9", "sid": "1PE 3:9"}, "not rendering evil for evil, or insult for insult; but instead blessing, knowing that you were called to this, that you\nmay inherit a blessing. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "10", "sid": "1PE 3:10"}, "For, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": ["\u201cHe who would love life \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["and see good days, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": ["let him keep his tongue from evil \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["and his lips from speaking deceit. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "11", "sid": "1PE 3:11"}, "Let him turn away from evil and do good. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["Let him seek peace and pursue it. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "12", "sid": "1PE 3:12"}, "For the eyes of the Lord are on the righteous, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["and his ears open to their prayer; \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["but the face of the Lord is against those who do evil.\u201d", {"type": "note", "marker": "x", "content": [{"type": "char", "marker": "xo", "content": ["3:12 "]}, {"type": "char", "marker": "xt", "content": ["Zabur 34:12-16"]}], "caller": "+"}, " \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "13", "sid": "1PE 3:13"}, "Now who will harm you if you become imitators of that which is good?\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "14", "sid": "1PE 3:14"}, "But even if you should suffer for righteousness\u2019 sake, you are blessed. \u201cDon\u2019t fear what they fear, neither be\ntroubled.\u201d", {"type": "note", "marker": "x", "content": [{"type": "char", "marker": "xo", "content": ["3:14 "]}, {"type": "char", "marker": "xt", "content": ["Isaiah 8:12"]}], "caller": "+"}, " \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "15", "sid": "1PE 3:15"}, "But sanctify the Lord Allah in your hearts. Always be ready to give an answer to everyone who asks you a reason\nconcerning the hope that is in you, with humility and fear, \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "16", "sid": "1PE 3:16"}, "having a good conscience. Thus, while you are spoken against as evildoers, they may be disappointed who curse your good\nway of life in Masih. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "17", "sid": "1PE 3:17"}, "For it is better, if it is Allah\u2019s will, that you suffer for doing well than for doing evil.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "18", "sid": "1PE 3:18"}, "Because Masih also suffered for sins once, the righteous for the unrighteous, that he might bring you to Allah, being put\nto death in the flesh, but made alive in the Spirit, \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "19", "sid": "1PE 3:19"}, "in whom he also went and preached to the spirits in prison,\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "20", "sid": "1PE 3:20"}, "who before were disobedient, when Allah waited patiently in the days of Nuh, while the ship was being built. In it, few,\nthat is, eight souls, were saved through water. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "21", "sid": "1PE 3:21"}, "This is a symbol of baptism, which now saves you\u2014not the putting away of the filth of the flesh, but the answer of a good\nconscience towards Allah, through the resurrection of Al Masih Isa,\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "22", "sid": "1PE 3:22"}, "who is at the right hand of Allah, having gone into heaven, angels and authorities and powers being made subject to him.\n"]}, {"type": "chapter", "marker": "c", "number": "4", "sid": "1PE 4"}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "1", "sid": "1PE 4:1"}, "Therefore, since Masih suffered for us in the flesh, arm yourselves also with the same mind; for he who has suffered in\nthe flesh has ceased from sin, \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "2", "sid": "1PE 4:2"}, "that you no longer should live the rest of your time in the flesh for the lusts of men, but for the will of Allah.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "3", "sid": "1PE 4:3"}, "For we have spent enough of our past time doing the desire of the Gentiles, and having walked in lewdness, lusts, drunken\nbinges, orgies, carousings, and abominable idolatries. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "4", "sid": "1PE 4:4"}, "They think it is strange that you don\u2019t run with them into the same excess of riot, blaspheming.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "5", "sid": "1PE 4:5"}, "They will give account to him who is ready to judge the living and the dead.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "6", "sid": "1PE 4:6"}, "For to this end the Good News was preached even to the dead, that they might be judged indeed as men in the flesh, but\nlive as to Allah in the spirit. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "7", "sid": "1PE 4:7"}, "But the end of all things is near. Therefore be of sound mind, self-controlled, and sober in prayer.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "8", "sid": "1PE 4:8"}, "And above all things be earnest in your love amongst yourselves, for love covers a multitude of sins.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "9", "sid": "1PE 4:9"}, "Be hospitable to one another without grumbling. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "10", "sid": "1PE 4:10"}, "As each has received a gift, employ it in serving one another, as good managers of the grace of Allah in its various\nforms. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "11", "sid": "1PE 4:11"}, "If anyone speaks, let it be as it were the very words of Allah. If anyone serves, let it be as of the strength which\nAllah supplies, that in all things Allah may be glorified through Al Masih Isa, to whom belong the glory and the dominion\nforever and ever. Amen. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "12", "sid": "1PE 4:12"}, "Beloved, don\u2019t be astonished at the fiery trial which has come upon you to test you, as though a strange thing happened\nto you. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "13", "sid": "1PE 4:13"}, "But because you are partakers of Masih\u2019s sufferings, rejoice, that at the revelation of his glory you also may rejoice\nwith exceeding joy. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "14", "sid": "1PE 4:14"}, "If you are insulted for the name of Masih, you are blessed; because the Spirit of glory and of Allah rests on you. On\ntheir part he is blasphemed, but on your part he is glorified. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "15", "sid": "1PE 4:15"}, "For let none of you suffer as a murderer, or a thief, or an evil doer, or a meddler in other men\u2019s matters.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "16", "sid": "1PE 4:16"}, "But if one of you suffers for being a Christian, let him not be ashamed; but let him glorify Allah in this matter.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "17", "sid": "1PE 4:17"}, "For the time has come for judgement to begin with the household of Allah. If it begins first with us, what will happen to\nthose who don\u2019t obey the Good News of Allah? \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "18", "sid": "1PE 4:18"}, "\u201cIf it is hard for the righteous to be saved, what will happen to the ungodly and the\nsinner?\u201d", {"type": "note", "marker": "x", "content": [{"type": "char", "marker": "xo", "content": ["4:18 "]}, {"type": "char", "marker": "xt", "content": ["Proverbs 11:31"]}], "caller": "+"}, " \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "19", "sid": "1PE 4:19"}, "Therefore let them also who suffer according to the will of Allah in doing good entrust their souls to him, as to a\nfaithful Creator. \n"]}, {"type": "chapter", "marker": "c", "number": "5", "sid": "1PE 5"}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "1", "sid": "1PE 5:1"}, "Therefore I exhort the elders amongst you, as a fellow elder, and a witness of the sufferings of Masih, and who will also\nshare in the glory that will be revealed. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "2", "sid": "1PE 5:2"}, "Shepherd the flock of Allah which is amongst you, exercising the oversight, not under compulsion, but voluntarily, not for\ndishonest gain, but willingly; \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "3", "sid": "1PE 5:3"}, "not as lording it over those entrusted to you, but making yourselves examples to the flock.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "4", "sid": "1PE 5:4"}, "When the chief Shepherd is revealed, you will receive the crown of glory that doesn\u2019t fade away.\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "5", "sid": "1PE 5:5"}, "Likewise, you younger ones, be subject to the elder. Yes, all of you clothe yourselves with humility, to subject\nyourselves to one another; for \u201cAllah resists the proud, but gives grace to the\nhumble.\u201d", {"type": "note", "marker": "x", "content": [{"type": "char", "marker": "xo", "content": ["5:5 "]}, {"type": "char", "marker": "xt", "content": ["Proverbs 3:34 "]}], "caller": "+"}, " \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "6", "sid": "1PE 5:6"}, "Humble yourselves therefore under the mighty hand of Allah, that he may exalt you in due time,\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "7", "sid": "1PE 5:7"}, "casting all your worries on him, because he cares for you. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "8", "sid": "1PE 5:8"}, "Be sober and self-controlled. Be watchful. Your adversary, the Iblis, walks around like a roaring lion, seeking whom he\nmay devour. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "9", "sid": "1PE 5:9"}, "Withstand him steadfast in your faith, knowing that your brothers who are in the world are undergoing the same sufferings.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "10", "sid": "1PE 5:10"}, "But may Allah of all grace, who called you to his eternal glory by Masih Isa, after you have suffered a little while,\nperfect, establish, strengthen, and settle you. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "11", "sid": "1PE 5:11"}, "To him be the glory and the power forever and ever. Amen. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "12", "sid": "1PE 5:12"}, "Through Silvanus, our faithful brother, as I consider him, I have written to you briefly, exhorting, and testifying that\nthis is the true grace of Allah in which you stand. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "13", "sid": "1PE 5:13"}, "She who is in Babylon, chosen together with you, greets you. So does Marqus, my son.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "14", "sid": "1PE 5:14"}, "Greet one another with a kiss of love. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": ["Peace be to all of you who are in Masih Isa. Amen. "]}]}